"title": "5152: fingers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5152",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Parts of the hand used in various kinds of activity, both good and bad. They were prominent in the OT sacrificial ritual, and were also used as a symbol for authority, accusation and minimum effort.</p>\n<h2>Regular activities using the fingers</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:1\">PSA 144:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:19\">PRO 31:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:5\">SNG 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Fingers used in sacrificial ritual</h2>\n<h3>In the consecration of priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:12\">EXO 29:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:15\">LEV 8:15</a></p>\n<h3>In the ritual for the sin offering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:6\">LEV 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:17\">LEV 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:25\">LEV 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:30\">LEV 4:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:34\">LEV 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:9\">LEV 9:9</a></p>\n<h3>In the ritual of the Day of Atonement</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:14\">LEV 16:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:19\">LEV 16:19</a></p>\n<h3>In cleansing rituals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:16\">LEV 14:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:4\">NUM 19:4</a></p>\n<h2>The finger as a unit of measurement</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:21\">JER 52:21</a></p>\n<h2>Deformed fingers</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:20\">2SA 21:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr20:6\">1CH 20:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's fingers</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ heals with his fingers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:32-Mark7:35\">MRK 7:32–7:35</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ writes with his fingers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:6\">JHN 8:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:5\">DAN 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Proving Jesus Christ's resurrection</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:25\">JHN 20:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:27\">JHN 20:27</a></p>\n<h2>Evil done with the fingers</h2>\n<h3>Idolatrous worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:8\">ISA 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:8\">ISA 17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:3\">ISA 59:3</a></p>\n<h3>Making accusations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:9\">ISA 58:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:12-Prov6:13\">PRO 6:12–6:13</a></p>\n<h3>Doing harm</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:12\">JOB 1:12</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Fingers used in symbolic actions</h2>\n<h3>The finger ring as a sign of authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:42\">GEN 41:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:10\">EST 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:2\">EST 8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:22\">LUK 15:22</a></p>\n<h3>The finger as a symbol of minimal effort</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:4\">MAT 23:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:10\">1KI 12:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:10\">2CH 10:10</a> <em>Rehoboam refusing to lift the burdens placed on the people by his father Solomon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:46\">LUK 11:46</a></p>\n<h3>The finger as a visible reminder</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:2-Prov7:3\">PRO 7:2–7:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:8\">DEU 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:18\">DEU 11:18</a></p>",
